1
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,200
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,360
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,360
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 3]

23
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:51,440
[Huamao Tower]

24
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:53,600
Let's go, Qian.

25
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:55,560
You go ahead. I have to work late.

26
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:00,960
Mentor.

27
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,320
What are you doing here?

28
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:03,480
Investigating

29
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:04,960
without permission
is against the rules.

30
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:07,480
Aren't you here, too?

31
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:08,920
I saw you get on the airport bus,

32
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:10,520
and I knew you were up to something.

33
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:12,880
So if you're not looking into it,
I can't either?

34
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:16,680
Did what I said go in one ear
and out the other?

35
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,120
How many times have I told you?

36
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:19,680
We have no authority
to investigate others.

37
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,480
I just ran into him.

38
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:25,880
Do you believe that yourself?

39
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:27,280
A chance encounter? Seriously?

40
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:28,520
Tell me.

41
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:30,160
Even if you stop Qian Shengkai,

42
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:30,960
what will you do?

43
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:31,880
Threaten or coax him?

44
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,080
Of course not!

45
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:35,960
I'll reason with him

46
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:36,880
and get him to talk.

47
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:37,600
First,

48
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:39,280
if you question him,

49
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,360
that's against the rules.

50
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:42,720
Secondly, even if you could do this,

51
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,520
don't you think it's a childish trick?

52
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:46,360
Which suspect will listen to you?

53
00:02:46,440 --> 00:02:48,360
Reason with him?

54
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:50,840
Then why do police need evidence

55
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:51,760
or investigations at all?

56
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:55,960
What if he comes to us and confesses?

57
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:57,480
That wouldn't break the rules, right?

58
00:02:58,280 --> 00:02:59,440
Mentor, go and tail him.

59
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:00,200
I'll be right back.

60
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:01,280
Come back!

61
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:02,680
You…!

62
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:23,480
Hey, honey.

63
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:26,280
I have to work late again.

64
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:29,560
I'll be home late.

65
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,240
You and Tian don't wait for me.

66
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:33,840
Want a late-night snack?

67
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:34,640
I'll bring some back.

68
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,000
Okay.

69
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:39,400
I'll hang up now.

70
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:40,720
Bye-bye.

71
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:54,000
Sorry, the number you dialed
is not in service.

72
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,240
Please check and try again.

73
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:30,120
Hey…

74
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:31,800
Over here.

75
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:34,880
Mentor.

76
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:35,680
It's me.

77
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,360
Dressed like this,

78
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,080
are you worried

79
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:43,360
Qian Shengkai won't notice you?

80
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:45,680
I'm trying to make sure he notices me.

81
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:47,960
Where is he?

82
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:48,640
I don't know.

83
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:50,280
Didn't I ask you to tail him?

84
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:52,600
Men…

85
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:53,600
Mentor.

86
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,640
Don't call me that.

87
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:58,200
I'm sorry.

88
00:04:58,520 --> 00:04:59,200
I panicked.

89
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:03,880
Think back.

90
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:05,800
He

91
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:08,280
wasn't carrying anything
when he went downstairs, right?

92
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:10,600
When he greeted a coworker,

93
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:11,760
he pointed upstairs.

94
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,760
What he meant was

95
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,000
he'd be right back.

96
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,240
So I think

97
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,000
he just went to grab a bite

98
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,320
and would be back soon.

99
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:25,280
You didn't even notice that?

100
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:26,240
I…

101
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:27,520
I…

102
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:28,320
Men…

103
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,440
Mentor, you…

104
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:31,160
You've gotta teach me

105
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:32,480
how to size people up at a glance.

106
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:34,760
How come I don't notice any of that?

107
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,720
Alright, tell me.

108
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:40,920
What are you going to do in this outfit?

109
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:42,840
I'm all covered up

110
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,880
because Qian Shengkai
once saw me at the airport.

111
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,200
I can't let him recognize me.

112
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,000
As for what comes next,

113
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:48,880
whatever I say,

114
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:50,640
just play along, okay?

115
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:27,480
Here he comes.

116
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,400
Excuse me!

117
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,800
Point behind you.

118
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,000
Good!

119
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:53,920
He should've seen me.

120
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:55,720
I am

121
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,640
Shizuko Nishimura.

122
00:06:58,080 --> 00:06:59,880
I can keep bowing if I have to.

123
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,000
A full 90-degree bow.

124
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:01,640
I really can.

125
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:02,720
Alright, let's go.

126
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,640
How did you come up with that idea?

127
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:13,000
Qian Shengkai has a decent job

128
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,520
that pays well.

129
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:17,000
So he's different
from professional smugglers.

130
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,040
After his failure this time,

131
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,760
he must be really anxious,
maybe even panicking.

132
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:23,560
And I remember,
outside the passenger inspection room,

133
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,400
he must have seen Shizuko Nishimura.

134
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:26,680
Even if he doesn't understand Japanese,

135
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,840
he must've seen
that genetic sample container.

136
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:30,800
So he basically figured out

137
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:31,800
that he and this Japanese woman

138
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,000
were in the same line of work.

139
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:35,480
So I deliberately let him see

140
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,880
a Japanese-speaking woman with you.

141
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,200
If he wants to confirm

142
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,120
whether he'll get

143
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:42,080
dragged into a follow-up investigation,

144
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:43,440
he'll have no choice

145
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:44,440
but to come to us.

146
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,440
Are you that sure?

147
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:46,760
Not really.

148
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:48,320
But

149
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,480
we're already here.

150
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:51,760
Might as well scare him,
or this trip's for nothing.

151
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:53,240
Let me say this again.

152
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,280
No more unauthorized actions

153
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:56,320
or breaking discipline.

154
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,400
Got it?

155
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:58,560
Yes, Mentor.

156
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:00,280
Get in.

157
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:33,640
Thanks, Mentor.

158
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:34,160
I'm off, then.

159
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:34,680
Don't mention it.

160
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:35,240
Bye-bye.

161
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:58,680
[Your Japanese is pretty good.
Keep it up.]

162
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:01,040
Thanks, Mentor.

163
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:16,640
Did you figure out the problem
I gave you yesterday?

164
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:17,760
Little yellow flower.

165
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,360
Shihuo came up with a good one.

166
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:22,800
It even stumped Bowen.

167
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,400
You know what?

168
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:26,200
Your mentor is proof of that saying,

169
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:28,760
"Men who talk less are
impressive types."

170
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,920
If you don't buy it, try again.

171
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,240
Check this out.

172
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,280
Watch your head.

173
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:36,120
Okay.

174
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:36,760
It's fine.

175
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:37,760
What are they playing?

176
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:40,000
It's a really boring game.

177
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,360
They like to play this
before and after every shift.

178
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:43,960
Basically,

179
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:45,320
there is a picture.

180
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,760
You cover up one corner of it

181
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:48,560
and try to guess what's hidden there.

182
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:49,640
Your mentor

183
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:50,520
came up with this game.

184
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:51,560
My mentor?

185
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:54,400
That sounds interesting.

186
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:55,360
I'll go check it out.

187
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:57,240
It's really boring.

188
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:58,920
Hey…

189
00:09:58,920 --> 00:09:59,720
Hey!

190
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:00,840
What are you doing here?

191
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:02,120
- Count me in.
- I'm taking my pants off!

192
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,240
No, I mean the game
you guys are playing.

193
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:05,200
Let me join.

194
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,960
Are you sure you want to play?

195
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:07,720
Seriously?

196
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:08,560
Seriously.

197
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:10,160
Come on, then.

198
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:11,440
No problem.

199
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:15,360
Everyone in our section
has to know how to play it.

200
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:17,120
Your mentor came up with it.

201
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:18,240
What is this?

202
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:20,560
Butterfly.

203
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:21,960
It's not that simple!

204
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,880
You need to be precise
about origin and species.

205
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:28,600
- Three, two, one. - Origin…

206
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:29,120
And species…

207
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,200
Morpho Helena,

208
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:31,400
from the Amazon River Basin
in South America.

209
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,520
Bingo.

210
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:34,840
Another round?

211
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:37,920
I'm not afraid of getting crushed.

212
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:39,240
Getting crushed is how you improve.

213
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:39,640
Come on!

214
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:41,000
Just like your mentor.

215
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:42,440
Hold on.

216
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:44,920
Shihuo came up with one yesterday

217
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,440
that even Bowen couldn't get.

218
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:46,960
This one!

219
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:48,280
What is it?

220
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:49,360
Little yellow flower.

221
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,000
What is it?

222
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:54,520
Hurry up.

223
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:54,960
China rose…

224
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:55,600
No.

225
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:56,880
Rose! Rose!

226
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:57,240
Ro…

227
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:58,160
What kind of rose?

228
00:10:58,520 --> 00:10:59,000
Hi, Mentor.

229
00:10:59,120 --> 00:10:59,760
What rose is it?

230
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:00,840
Dancing Girl of Izu

231
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:02,400
- from Japan.
- Dancing Girl of Izu from Japan.

232
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:03,760
Come on, Mr. Guo.

233
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:04,360
That's cheating.

234
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,160
Don't leave it here.

235
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,440
My trainee's too weak. I had to help.

236
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:10,880
Mr. Guo just doesn't want us

237
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:11,800
- making fun of his trainee.
- Hello, Passenger Inspection Section I.

238
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:13,600
He came all this way
just to get some exercise.

239
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:14,680
Looking for Mr. Guo?

240
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:15,880
That's how your mentor is.

241
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:16,560
He's hard

242
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:17,440
on you,

243
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:18,960
but the second outsiders are around,

244
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,920
- he gets really protective.
- Mr. Guo, you have a call.

245
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:22,600
Coming.

246
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:24,160
Check this out.

247
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:26,520
What is this?

248
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:28,240
- This is a… - Banana tree.

249
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:29,360
Right!

250
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,720
I-I was just about to say that!

251
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:32,920
Hello, this is Guo Cong.

252
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:34,600
Just about to say…

253
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,240
Mr. Qian?

254
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,720
You wanted to talk to me?

255
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:39,320
Now?

256
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:40,600
Okay.

257
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:42,360
At the Airport Cafe.

258
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:43,720
See you later.

259
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:44,520
Bye.

260
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:50,160
You were right.

261
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:51,120
Qian Shengkai is here.

262
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,160
So it really is him?

263
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:55,200
Mentor, wait for me!

264
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:04,840
Sorry, Mr. Guo.

265
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:05,880
I always forget to put up the sign.

266
00:12:05,880 --> 00:12:07,200
It's okay. Just remember next time.

267
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:08,480
Wouldn't want a passenger to slip.

268
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:09,280
Okay, sure.

269
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:09,640
Thanks.

270
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:10,200
It's alright.

271
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:11,400
Mr. Guo.

272
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:13,640
Good work, Liu.

273
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:40,280
Mr. Guo.

274
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:41,600
Mr. Qian.

275
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:43,120
Hello.

276
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:45,120
Hello.

277
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:51,040
Mr. Guo.

278
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:52,920
Sorry to bother you both.

279
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,120
Can I ask you something?

280
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:57,640
Did you also let

281
00:12:57,760 --> 00:12:58,880
that foreign woman go?

282
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:04,760
Mr. Qian, that involves

283
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,400
Customs' investigative procedures,

284
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:07,920
so we can't disclose it.

285
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:09,920
Here's the thing.

286
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:12,840
I think I saw her outside
the other day.

287
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,560
The guy she was with

288
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:17,000
looked a little like you.

289
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:19,200
Mr. Guo,

290
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:20,920
is he talking about you…

291
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:21,560
Zhang Yu.

292
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:24,360
Don't you know we can't
discuss investigation progress

293
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:25,040
with outsiders?

294
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:26,560
Mr. Guo,

295
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:28,600
how am I an outsider?

296
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:30,760
Mr. Qian,

297
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:32,520
I remember you said

298
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:33,920
you bought that thermos

299
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:35,400
from a random street stall.

300
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:37,800
You didn't know
it had a hidden compartment

301
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,840
or what was inside it,

302
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:40,360
right?

303
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:41,440
So,

304
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:43,880
at this stage of the case,

305
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:45,000
you are an outsider.

306
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:45,920
Of course,

307
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:47,520
as the case develops

308
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:48,800
and more evidence turns up,

309
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:49,720
that could change.

310
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:50,280
What do you think?

311
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:56,080
I just want to know
how the case is progressing.

312
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:58,440
After all, I'm involved.

313
00:13:58,600 --> 00:13:59,520
We really can't disclose

314
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,840
the progress of the investigation.

315
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:04,720
But as the saying goes,

316
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,040
"Confess for leniency;

317
00:14:06,040 --> 00:14:07,320
resist for harsher punishment.

318
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:10,560
Make amends for a lighter sentence."

319
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:15,720
Mr. Qian,

320
00:14:16,560 --> 00:14:18,200
if someone's been using you,

321
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,880
there's no need to cover for them.

322
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:21,000
Actually, that foreign traveler…

323
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:21,800
Zhang Yu.

324
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,520
Do you ever listen to what I say?

325
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:25,640
Mentor,

326
00:14:26,280 --> 00:14:28,880
I think Mr. Qian is willing
to cooperate.

327
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:31,440
Let's give him a chance.

328
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:35,000
Here's the thing, Mr. Qian.

329
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:37,560
If you tell us everything,

330
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:38,640
it'll make things easier.

331
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:41,520
You didn't know anything about this,

332
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:42,640
and someone told you to do it,

333
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:43,440
right?

334
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:46,400
From what I can see,
you're living a pretty comfortable life.

335
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,000
So why get involved in smuggling?

336
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:50,280
There must've been a reason.

337
00:14:50,600 --> 00:14:52,360
Were you being threatened?

338
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,520
You're a victim in this,

339
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:55,520
aren't you?

340
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:56,600
Yeah, exactly!

341
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,040
Mr. Guo,

342
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,360
I'm a victim, too!

343
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:00,560
I was forced into it.

344
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:01,800
Yeah, yeah.

345
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,760
They say the middle class
gets ruined by bad investments.

346
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:10,120
I'm exactly that kind of case.

347
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:11,480
Things had been going

348
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:13,240
pretty smoothly for me.

349
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:15,040
But who doesn't want to make more money

350
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,920
and give their family a better life?

351
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,040
Back in March,

352
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:22,760
a friend of mine

353
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:23,520
got me to invest

354
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:24,840
in a blockchain project.

355
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:26,920
At first, I didn't put in much.

356
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:30,400
But the returns kept coming in
right on schedule.

357
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:32,560
So I put all my savings into it

358
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:34,400
and even borrowed from friends.

359
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,360
But who knew that in May,

360
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:37,840
the whole project just vanished.

361
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:40,920
I ended up buried in debt.

362
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:42,240
I didn't even dare tell my wife.

363
00:15:43,160 --> 00:15:44,360
Every day, I kept thinking

364
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:46,560
about how to cover the hole fast.

365
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:48,120
What does the guy
who had you deliver the goods

366
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:49,360
have to do with your creditors?

367
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:50,800
Nothing.

368
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:52,640
That guy

369
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:55,000
reached out to me online last month.

370
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:59,000
But he seemed to know me really well.

371
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:00,560
He knew exactly what I needed.

372
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:03,560
Just carrying a cup
would get me 20,000 yuan.

373
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:05,040
How could I possibly resist that?

374
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:07,640
But Mr. Guo, I swear

375
00:16:08,160 --> 00:16:10,200
I really thought
it was just a regular cup.

376
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:12,560
It was basically like

377
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:14,200
some shady boss hired me

378
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,800
to do a temp job for money.

379
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:17,520
I just did what they told me
and made the trip.

380
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:18,240
And…

381
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:19,520
And then

382
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:22,560
you caught me
before I even got on the plane.

383
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:27,720
Where did you get the thermos?

384
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:31,920
Well…

385
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:32,960
Um…

386
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:34,880
It's been so long.

387
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:36,960
I don't remember.

388
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:38,120
Mr. Qian,

389
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:40,080
I know you're lying.

390
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:41,400
You can go now.

391
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:43,600
Wait, Mr. Guo…

392
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:45,080
You can leave now.

393
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,960
Mr. Qian, still gambling on this?

394
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:00,480
I beg your pardon.

395
00:17:02,040 --> 00:17:04,440
You invested in blockchain
for huge returns,

396
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:06,720
even betting
your whole family's savings on it.

397
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:08,080
You knew carrying a cup

398
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:09,040
for 20,000 yuan

399
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:10,200
was fishy,

400
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:12,560
yet you still gambled
you'd get away with it.

401
00:17:12,840 --> 00:17:14,160
And now you still want to gamble.

402
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:16,040
You're betting
that we won't find the handler,

403
00:17:16,040 --> 00:17:17,560
so you can walk away scot-free.

404
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:18,120
Right?

405
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:19,320
But I'm telling you,

406
00:17:19,320 --> 00:17:19,920
Mr. Qian.

407
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:23,280
All gamblers end up the same way.

408
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:24,120
They lose.

409
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:25,960
They lose everything.

410
00:17:32,120 --> 00:17:32,800
Mr. Guo,

411
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,560
if I tell you everything,

412
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:36,640
will I really be okay?

413
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:42,200
Mr. Qian.

414
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:45,040
Like we said earlier,

415
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:46,400
we're willing to believe

416
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:47,960
you're a victim.

417
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:49,800
So if you tell us the truth,

418
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:51,320
you still have a chance.

419
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:55,080
I'll talk.

420
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:57,480
After I agreed to deliver the goods,

421
00:17:57,760 --> 00:17:58,840
I got a call.

422
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:00,640
Then I drove

423
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:02,280
to a small alley on Mingjing Road.

424
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:04,720
But no one was there.

425
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:06,480
The money

426
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:08,400
was already in a trash can.

427
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:11,600
I got the cup

428
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:12,440
and the suitcase

429
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:14,040
from the trunk of a car that morning.

430
00:18:18,280 --> 00:18:20,000
All the steps
and what I was supposed to say

431
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:21,440
[Warning!]
were printed out.

432
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:22,120
[Warning!]

433
00:18:22,120 --> 00:18:22,800
[Warning!]
It even told me

434
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,360
[Warning!]
to burn it after I read it.

435
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:29,120
While at the airport,

436
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:30,640
I received a photo.

437
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:34,480
This lady

438
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:36,520
was in the photo.

439
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:43,640
Just like Qian Shengkai,
Shizuko Nishimura

440
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,360
never saw her handler, either.

441
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:46,560
They were drawn

442
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:47,880
into this setup step by step.

443
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:49,000
Zhang Yu

444
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:51,120
got secretly photographed
on her first day at work.

445
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:52,360
In a very short time,

446
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,120
her photo

447
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:55,240
was seen and used
by the smuggling ring.

448
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:56,680
This shows that around us,

449
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:58,480
there are informants
planted by the ring.

450
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:06,040
The airport has
tens of thousands of staff,

451
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:08,440
and many departments and work areas

452
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:10,280
overlap with ours.

453
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:11,920
Sir!

454
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:12,880
Sir!

455
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:16,160
Mr. Shen,

456
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:16,960
Mr. Guo,

457
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:18,560
the doll appeared again.

458
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:29,000
Come on, everyone, quiet down.

459
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:31,360
Please cooperate
and don't crowd around here, okay?

460
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:32,400
Alright, move along.

461
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:33,360
Please cooperate.

462
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:38,640
I was here just now,

463
00:19:38,680 --> 00:19:39,800
about to wash my hands.

464
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:41,840
And your airport cleaners

465
00:19:41,840 --> 00:19:43,040
didn't refill the hand soap

466
00:19:43,040 --> 00:19:44,760
when it ran out.

467
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:46,600
That doll

468
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:48,200
was right on top of that trash can!

469
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:50,000
I thought some kid had put it there

470
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,000
messing around.

471
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:51,720
So I took a look.

472
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:53,920
That doll looked really creepy!

473
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:54,720
You know?

474
00:19:55,040 --> 00:19:56,000
Seriously, people

475
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,280
who design toys these days

476
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:59,080
must have something wrong with them.

477
00:19:59,560 --> 00:20:00,920
Why make a toy for kids

478
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:02,600
that creepy?

479
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,160
It scared me to death.

480
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:05,880
I was washing up over there,

481
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:07,640
and it suddenly made a sound!

482
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:13,160
You can't catch me.

483
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:14,920
Good thing

484
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:16,080
I'm pretty tough!

485
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:17,600
You know, if it'd been someone else,

486
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:18,960
someone in poor shape,

487
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:19,560
with heart issues

488
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:20,320
or high blood pressure,

489
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:22,760
they could've dropped right there!

490
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:24,120
The airport would've been liable,

491
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:24,880
you know?

492
00:20:25,120 --> 00:20:25,720
Excuse me.

493
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:26,400
Sir,

494
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:28,280
how exactly did the doll sound?

495
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:29,200
That doll…

496
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:32,080
First it let out this creepy laugh,

497
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:33,560
just like in one of those

498
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:34,560
horror movies!

499
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:36,040
You can't catch me.

500
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:40,120
You can't catch me.

501
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:40,960
I can't remember

502
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:41,760
which movie it was.

503
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:44,520
Anyway, they definitely
used some kind of voice effect.

504
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:46,040
They made the sound really eerie.

505
00:20:46,080 --> 00:20:47,200
That doll's voice

506
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:48,840
must've played five or six times.

507
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:50,440
Then it started laughing again!

508
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:53,880
You can't catch me.

509
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:57,000
I could tell right away it was a prank.

510
00:20:57,120 --> 00:20:58,560
It scared a guy so badly

511
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:00,040
that he nearly peed his pants.

512
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:01,120
So I ran away

513
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,280
and called you right away.

514
00:21:02,320 --> 00:21:03,960
I even kept people away from the area!

515
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:07,000
I see you're all wearing those big caps.

516
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,480
Could this doll be aimed at you guys?

517
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:09,280
I told you!

518
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:11,200
I've seen plenty of those

519
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:12,000
horrible movies!

520
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:13,240
Oh my God.

521
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:15,040
This has nothing to do
with today's flights, right?

522
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,600
Will this doll affect today's flights?

523
00:21:16,640 --> 00:21:17,800
I'm in a hurry!

524
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:18,200
I…

525
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:19,600
Sir,

526
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:20,520
please don't panic.

527
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:21,640
And please don't

528
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:22,880
make baseless guesses.

529
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:25,080
You also don't need to worry

530
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:25,880
about flight safety.

531
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:28,000
And about what happened today,

532
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:29,080
please keep it to yourself.

533
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:31,280
Okay.

534
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:34,320
But I already took pictures
and posted them online!

535
00:21:34,360 --> 00:21:34,800
Well…

536
00:21:35,080 --> 00:21:36,960
A lot of people took pictures, too!

537
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:38,080
Then please cooperate with us

538
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:38,800
and delete them.

539
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:39,760
Hello, sir.

540
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:41,280
I'm Shen Xuejun from Airport Customs.

541
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:43,800
Can I take a look at the doll?

542
00:21:43,920 --> 00:21:44,280
Okay.

543
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:45,120
Thank you.

544
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:00,520
A basic cell phone was taped
to the doll's back.

545
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:02,280
It was probably set with an alarm.

546
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:03,960
That child's voice was the ringtone.

547
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:05,360
Sir,

548
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,880
could you show us the front again?

549
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:12,000
I've checked

550
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,320
these two dolls online.

551
00:22:13,480 --> 00:22:14,520
Their brooches

552
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:15,760
are clearly

553
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:17,000
added later.

554
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:20,480
They look very similar
to our customs emblem,

555
00:22:20,560 --> 00:22:22,360
the staff of Hermes, the Merchant God.

556
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:27,080
Okay, thanks.

557
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:57,960
Cong,

558
00:22:58,560 --> 00:23:00,360
what worried you before
isn't just a worry anymore.

559
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:01,800
The appearance of this doll

560
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:02,880
proves

561
00:23:03,560 --> 00:23:05,800
the Gene Case is closely linked
to Group E.

562
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:07,120
Could it be

563
00:23:07,560 --> 00:23:09,360
that Group E is really
making a comeback?

564
00:23:09,880 --> 00:23:11,120
I have my doubts, too.

565
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:12,760
They're both dolls.

566
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:14,120
But the dolls three years ago

567
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:16,000
appeared before Group E's operation

568
00:23:16,080 --> 00:23:17,320
with a strong sense of provocation.

569
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:19,840
This time, the doll
showed up after the action,

570
00:23:20,080 --> 00:23:21,960
and the action even failed.

571
00:23:22,080 --> 00:23:23,800
It's really puzzling.

572
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:25,360
Please stand firm and hold on…

573
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:27,440
Could this be to stir up panic
after the smuggling failed?

574
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:28,360
Please make way.

575
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:29,480
Liu.

576
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:30,120
Mr. Guo.

577
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:32,040
You've worked hard.

578
00:23:32,280 --> 00:23:32,800
Just doing my job.

579
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:33,800
I'm in a hurry.

580
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:34,960
I've gotta go.

581
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:37,320
They are just dolls, anyway.

582
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:38,440
No matter how scary they are,

583
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,640
the panic they can cause is limited.

584
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:43,320
A smuggling ring this careful

585
00:23:43,640 --> 00:23:45,440
wouldn't do something so boring

586
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:46,600
and pointless.

587
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:48,240
There's another thing
that doesn't add up.

588
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,200
Before, it was all about drugs.

589
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:51,840
Now it's blood genetic samples.

590
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:53,560
So these dolls

591
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:55,120
must mean something else.

592
00:23:55,280 --> 00:23:56,200
It's not a provocation.

593
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:57,200
It's a warning.

594
00:23:58,200 --> 00:23:59,560
Details of the doll case

595
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:02,000
have been strictly limited to insiders.

596
00:24:02,560 --> 00:24:03,600
So whoever placed the dolls

597
00:24:04,120 --> 00:24:05,960
must have something to do
with what happened three years ago.

598
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:07,440
What was the motive?

599
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:09,800
What you said about a warning
is interesting.

600
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,040
A warning about what?

601
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,040
No matter what,

602
00:24:13,080 --> 00:24:15,320
we intercepted the genetic sample.

603
00:24:16,360 --> 00:24:18,320
So this smuggling ring

604
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:20,000
won't back down that easily.

605
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:21,800
Like I said,

606
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:23,800
as long as we hold this line,

607
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,240
we can stay steady through it all.

608
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:26,040
Go back

609
00:24:26,520 --> 00:24:28,320
and brief Section I.

610
00:24:28,360 --> 00:24:28,880
I'll report this

611
00:24:29,040 --> 00:24:29,800
to the higher-ups

612
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:32,000
and tell the others to stay alert.

613
00:24:32,320 --> 00:24:32,560
Understood.

614
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:52,120
Over the past six months,

615
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:53,800
Group E has kept

616
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:55,040
coming up empty in our area,

617
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:56,200
over and over again,

618
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:57,600
and leaving traces behind.

619
00:24:57,880 --> 00:25:00,360
In the end,
under our superiors' command,

620
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:02,280
we tracked them back to their base

621
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:04,320
and wiped it out completely.

622
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:08,040
But it's weird.

623
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:10,840
They kept pushing into our section

624
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:13,560
and even used a doll
as a warning ahead of time.

625
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:15,440
Wasn't that just asking to get caught?

626
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:17,360
That doesn't fit criminal psychology.

627
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:19,120
Isn't it like in the movies,

628
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:20,560
where some criminals

629
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:21,880
like provoking the police?

630
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:24,200
I think the people in Group E

631
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:24,840
are just obsessed.

632
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,440
What were they after, then?

633
00:25:26,880 --> 00:25:29,560
Those criminals are in it to smuggle,

634
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:30,960
not to pick a fight.

635
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:34,120
If Section I is a hard nut to crack,

636
00:25:34,280 --> 00:25:36,640
they should've gone around it.

637
00:25:37,480 --> 00:25:38,840
Psychologically,

638
00:25:38,920 --> 00:25:41,120
people tend to rise where they fell,

639
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:43,200
but that behavior is actually rare,

640
00:25:43,240 --> 00:25:45,480
especially among criminals.

641
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:47,040
So?

642
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:48,840
Why do you think it is?

643
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:52,600
I… I am just guessing,

644
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:53,080
Mentor.

645
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:54,280
It's fine.

646
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:55,080
Go ahead.

647
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:00,440
First, I think

648
00:26:01,840 --> 00:26:03,440
Group E wouldn't limit itself

649
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,840
to smuggling

650
00:26:04,840 --> 00:26:06,200
only when Section I is on duty.

651
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:07,440
They must've been operating

652
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:09,120
at other times as well.

653
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:11,840
But the dolls only appeared

654
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:13,160
when a smuggling case

655
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:14,680
was about to happen in Section I.

656
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:16,400
So, could it be

657
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:17,680
that someone was using

658
00:26:17,720 --> 00:26:20,200
these dolls to help Section I

659
00:26:20,240 --> 00:26:22,480
link all these cases together?

660
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:24,960
To some extent,

661
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:27,960
that person was actually helping customs

662
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:29,640
take down the criminal ring.

663
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:33,200
Wow,
Zhang Yu's imagination is impressive.

664
00:26:33,880 --> 00:26:34,840
So you mean

665
00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:36,880
there's a mole among them

666
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:38,640
who's had a change of heart?

667
00:26:39,240 --> 00:26:40,480
Dayu, hold on.

668
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:41,600
Let her finish.

669
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:44,640
Is it possible

670
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:47,680
that the dolls back then
weren't provocation,

671
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,440
but rather

672
00:26:49,760 --> 00:26:50,480
early warnings?

673
00:26:53,240 --> 00:26:54,040
That makes sense.

674
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:57,040
Shihuo, that didn't help at all.

675
00:26:57,640 --> 00:26:59,320
Zhang Yu actually has a point.

676
00:26:59,840 --> 00:27:00,360
Yeah.

677
00:27:00,360 --> 00:27:02,400
My mentor
had a similar theory before.

678
00:27:02,800 --> 00:27:03,680
The core members

679
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:05,840
of Group E who were arrested back then

680
00:27:05,920 --> 00:27:07,480
only knew about the dolls,

681
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:09,400
but none of them
knew where they came from.

682
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:10,680
Three years ago,

683
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:13,640
every operation led by Sa Ziyi,
the head of Group E,

684
00:27:13,640 --> 00:27:14,960
was exposed by those dolls.

685
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:17,400
In the end, she had nowhere to run
and took her own life.

686
00:27:17,600 --> 00:27:20,440
So she definitely wasn't the one
who placed the dolls.

687
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:21,640
These dolls

688
00:27:22,320 --> 00:27:24,600
did seem to be aimed at Sa Ziyi.

689
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:27,400
So who exactly is this 'unseen' person
behind the dolls?

690
00:27:27,840 --> 00:27:29,960
We still don't know
whether they're friend or foe.

691
00:27:31,120 --> 00:27:33,600
And now the doll has shown up again.

692
00:27:34,280 --> 00:27:35,640
Could this person

693
00:27:36,040 --> 00:27:37,680
be warning us again?

694
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:39,400
A warning after the fact is pointless.

695
00:27:40,840 --> 00:27:41,880
After the fact?

696
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:45,040
Yeah!

697
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:46,400
After the fact!

698
00:27:47,280 --> 00:27:48,440
Let's all take a step back

699
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:49,640
and not get stuck in it.

700
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:51,080
What if

701
00:27:51,280 --> 00:27:52,720
there's someone else

702
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:53,840
who, just like us,

703
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:55,960
only found out
about the Gene Case afterward,

704
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:57,640
and only then placed the dolls?

705
00:27:58,640 --> 00:27:59,400
What does this mean?

706
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:02,400
He couldn't know
the exact timing of the crime.

707
00:28:02,480 --> 00:28:03,400
So it's very likely

708
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:04,400
he's not part of the ring.

709
00:28:05,240 --> 00:28:06,880
But he wants to bring them down.

710
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:08,080
So he used the dolls

711
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:09,200
to get our attention!

712
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:12,200
So, all in all,

713
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:13,640
I think this guy

714
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:15,680
is very likely trying to get them
from behind.

715
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:16,960
That makes sense.

716
00:28:17,760 --> 00:28:18,200
Shihuo,

717
00:28:18,280 --> 00:28:19,840
you've got the point this time.

718
00:28:19,840 --> 00:28:22,120
Whether it's the same person
as before or not,

719
00:28:22,120 --> 00:28:23,640
now that he's made a move,

720
00:28:23,640 --> 00:28:24,960
there'll definitely be more to come.

721
00:28:25,320 --> 00:28:26,280
Everyone, get ready.

722
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:27,360
Meeting in ten minutes.

723
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:27,960
Okay.

724
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:31,040
Mentor.

725
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:32,640
How do we investigate?

726
00:28:35,680 --> 00:28:37,800
I think you're in the wrong place.

727
00:28:39,240 --> 00:28:40,440
You should've been a detective.

728
00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:46,680
Thought I didn't want to?

729
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:07,880
Ziyi,

730
00:29:08,960 --> 00:29:10,560
I'll definitely find the killer.

731
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:17,840
I really miss

732
00:30:19,200 --> 00:30:20,080
that old guy.

733
00:30:46,840 --> 00:30:47,400
Ouch, ouch.

734
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:49,400
This, this spot. This spot hurts.

735
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:50,080
It hurts

736
00:30:50,080 --> 00:30:50,720
right here.

737
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:01,280
Mentor.

738
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:07,240
What's up?

739
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:08,000
Doctor,

740
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:09,520
can I ask you something?

741
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:11,720
Can I skip that shot?

742
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:15,600
What's wrong?

743
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:17,040
It hurts. It hurts so much.

744
00:31:18,640 --> 00:31:19,680
Okay, we'll skip it.

745
00:31:20,160 --> 00:31:20,880
Thank you.

746
00:31:22,120 --> 00:31:22,720
You two talk.

747
00:31:22,760 --> 00:31:24,640
I'll go take care of the others.

748
00:31:25,480 --> 00:31:26,080
Thank you.

749
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:28,600
Thank you.

750
00:31:28,600 --> 00:31:29,680
You're welcome.

751
00:31:51,240 --> 00:31:51,840
Song!

752
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:52,640
Coming!

753
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:53,560
Where's my notebook?

754
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:54,960
It's on the table.

755
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:56,400
The one you look for every day.

756
00:31:56,440 --> 00:31:57,200
On this table.

757
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:58,480
Here, here.

758
00:31:58,680 --> 00:32:00,160
I remember I put it in a drawer.

759
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:01,320
Is it this one?

760
00:32:01,360 --> 00:32:02,040
Yeah, right.

761
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:02,640
I'll get back.

762
00:32:02,640 --> 00:32:03,400
Okay, okay.

763
00:32:19,800 --> 00:32:20,680
What brings you here?

764
00:32:21,400 --> 00:32:23,320
Jiang Shihuo wanted to visit you, too.

765
00:32:23,880 --> 00:32:25,800
But he has a big family to take care of

766
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:26,840
and is tied up.

767
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:28,040
He gave me some money

768
00:32:28,040 --> 00:32:30,120
and asked me
to bring you something to eat.

769
00:32:36,520 --> 00:32:37,400
Isn't Jiang Shihuo

770
00:32:37,440 --> 00:32:38,360
attending the class?

771
00:32:38,600 --> 00:32:39,680
Did you skip class again?

772
00:32:40,240 --> 00:32:41,200
Nope.

773
00:32:41,720 --> 00:32:43,400
Guo Cong,
how many times have I told you?

774
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:46,400
This entry training program
only lasts a month.

775
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:47,640
And you're starting from zero.

776
00:32:47,640 --> 00:32:48,640
If you don't work harder,

777
00:32:48,640 --> 00:32:49,480
how are you going to compete

778
00:32:49,480 --> 00:32:51,400
with those customs academy grads?

779
00:33:03,400 --> 00:33:04,560
Report, Mr. Chen.

780
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:04,840
Go ahead.

781
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:07,280
It's Sunday today.

782
00:33:07,280 --> 00:33:08,880
You forgot and got the schedule wrong.

783
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:11,960
Sunday?

784
00:33:15,080 --> 00:33:16,880
I told you to practice
'size people up at a glance' on Sundays.

785
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:17,840
What are you doing here?

786
00:33:17,880 --> 00:33:19,320
It's been a while,

787
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:20,320
so I came to see you.

788
00:33:20,320 --> 00:33:21,160
I missed you.

789
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:24,560
What for?

790
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:25,880
I'm going back soon.

791
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:28,960
If I don't go back soon,
Shen Xuejun will go crazy.

792
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:31,800
He can't handle you naughty monkeys.

793
00:33:35,600 --> 00:33:36,800
Naughty monkeys?

794
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:42,120
If naughty monkeys exercise more,

795
00:33:42,120 --> 00:33:43,080
they can still become

796
00:33:43,080 --> 00:33:45,280
as sharp-eyed as Sun Wukong, right?

797
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:47,800
Have some water.

798
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:55,040
Mentor.

799
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:57,160
The air outside is really nice.

800
00:33:57,400 --> 00:33:58,640
Let me take you out for some fresh air.

801
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:03,840
Mentor!

802
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:04,400
Mentor!

803
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:06,200
Did you get leave from customs?

804
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:08,280
Yes.

805
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:09,000
Really?

806
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:10,040
Really.

807
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:10,400
Let's go.

808
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:10,880
Yes.

809
00:34:22,600 --> 00:34:23,240
This way.

810
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:26,000
Mentor!

811
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:04,120
Let me tell you something.

812
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:06,360
I'm also a mentor now.

813
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,000
I got a female trainee.

814
00:35:08,760 --> 00:35:11,640
But I don't really know how to teach.

815
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:14,360
You're the only mentor I've ever had.

816
00:35:16,480 --> 00:35:17,520
With your tough style,

817
00:35:17,520 --> 00:35:19,160
it's okay if I teach a male trainee.

818
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:20,400
But a girl…

819
00:35:21,360 --> 00:35:23,040
I'm not sure

820
00:35:23,360 --> 00:35:25,240
how to balance things.

821
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:26,640
Is she a newbie?

822
00:35:28,640 --> 00:35:29,560
Yes, yes.

823
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:30,520
A newbie…

824
00:35:33,640 --> 00:35:34,840
She's got great potential.

825
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:36,120
She studied psychology.

826
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:37,320
Way better than me.

827
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,600
I don't know if you still remember

828
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:41,480
Sa Ziyi.

829
00:35:42,600 --> 00:35:44,240
A few days ago,
there was a case at customs

830
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:45,760
that was a lot like

831
00:35:45,800 --> 00:35:47,280
the way Sa Ziyi operated back then.

832
00:35:48,440 --> 00:35:49,800
They also used a bunch of smokescreens.

833
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:51,480
But don't worry.

834
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:52,920
I caught them all.

835
00:35:53,720 --> 00:35:55,400
That doll appeared again.

836
00:35:57,720 --> 00:35:58,640
Doll? What doll?

837
00:36:01,360 --> 00:36:02,200
Did you catch them?

838
00:36:04,320 --> 00:36:04,920
Yes.

839
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:05,960
You must catch them!

840
00:36:09,320 --> 00:36:09,920
Cong,

841
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:13,480
you're about to become
an officer of China Customs,

842
00:36:14,080 --> 00:36:15,280
a national guard.

843
00:36:15,320 --> 00:36:16,880
What I expect from you is

844
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:18,840
loyalty, integrity, and responsibility.

845
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:19,400
Got it?

846
00:36:19,520 --> 00:36:20,280
Yes,

847
00:36:20,880 --> 00:36:21,600
Mentor.

848
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:26,480
[The Book of Songs ·
Lesser Court Hymns · Tian Bao]

849
00:36:26,480 --> 00:36:28,080
Chen, what are you looking for again?

850
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:30,240
It's 9 PM.

851
00:36:30,280 --> 00:36:30,840
Song,

852
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:32,560
since you're here, do me a favor.

853
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:35,000
I can't find my notebook.

854
00:36:35,040 --> 00:36:37,040
I need to write down
something important right now.

855
00:36:37,080 --> 00:36:38,720
Didn't I give it to you this morning?

856
00:36:39,720 --> 00:36:40,280
That's it.

857
00:36:41,440 --> 00:36:42,000
Is it this one?

858
00:36:42,120 --> 00:36:43,000
No, not that one.

859
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:43,880
Not this notebook.

860
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:46,320
There are many,
many notebooks piled together.

861
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:46,960
I keep…

862
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:49,400
I usually keep a diary,

863
00:36:49,560 --> 00:36:51,280
but I just can't remember
where I put it now.

864
00:36:54,600 --> 00:36:55,520
Look, is it this one?

865
00:36:58,240 --> 00:36:59,320
There are so many notebooks.

866
00:37:00,320 --> 00:37:01,040
This one?

867
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:04,520
Let me see.

868
00:37:07,440 --> 00:37:07,920
China…

869
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:10,400
This is it!

870
00:37:11,120 --> 00:37:12,200
Look at my memory…

871
00:37:12,760 --> 00:37:13,480
Song, you know what?

872
00:37:13,760 --> 00:37:15,880
These are all my work journals

873
00:37:16,080 --> 00:37:17,560
and my study notes.

874
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:19,880
You could say
my whole life is written in here.

875
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:21,880
You brought this suitcase here
back then.

876
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:23,800
I saw you left it there untouched,

877
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:25,200
so I put it away for you.

878
00:37:25,760 --> 00:37:26,160
No wonder…

879
00:37:26,640 --> 00:37:28,160
Thank you, thank you…

880
00:37:28,360 --> 00:37:29,520
Okay, I'll take my leave.

881
00:37:29,920 --> 00:37:30,280
Bye-bye.

882
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:30,720
Thanks, Song.

883
00:37:30,880 --> 00:37:31,560
You're welcome.

884
00:37:46,320 --> 00:37:46,840
Commendation Letter.

885
00:37:54,440 --> 00:37:58,440
Standing guard on the plateau
is not really hard work.

886
00:37:58,720 --> 00:38:00,240
Aside from the intense headaches

887
00:38:00,280 --> 00:38:01,960
caused by initial altitude sickness,

888
00:38:02,640 --> 00:38:04,440
everything else is fairly normal.

889
00:38:04,960 --> 00:38:06,920
Everything is peaceful.

890
00:38:07,440 --> 00:38:08,400
I'm just lonely.

891
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:12,840
There's a vulture
that comes by from time to time,

892
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:15,560
landing on a nearby rock
and watching me.

893
00:38:17,320 --> 00:38:18,160
"Watching me."

894
00:38:24,080 --> 00:38:26,360
[Dolls,
KM997, Drugs, Smuggling]

895
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:36,920
[Dolls → Poisonous Perfume,
E]

896
00:38:41,760 --> 00:38:42,440
Dolls?

897
00:38:44,320 --> 00:38:45,240
Group E?

898
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:56,520
[Four Years Ago
In 2019]

899
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:17,320
Qin!

900
00:39:18,240 --> 00:39:19,400
Where's the package for Mr. Zhao?

901
00:39:19,960 --> 00:39:21,040
On that courier table!

902
00:39:21,760 --> 00:39:22,800
Who sent it over?

903
00:39:23,240 --> 00:39:24,240
A courier.

904
00:39:24,720 --> 00:39:25,240
Okay!

905
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:40,640
Come in.

906
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:43,360
Mr. Zhao, your package is here.

907
00:39:44,040 --> 00:39:44,840
Package?

908
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:47,440
I didn't receive the courier call.

909
00:39:48,120 --> 00:39:49,360
Did they call the office?

910
00:39:49,600 --> 00:39:50,160
Nope.

911
00:39:50,200 --> 00:39:52,240
The gate security called me
to pick it up.

912
00:39:52,560 --> 00:39:53,920
It says, "For Mr. Zhao."

913
00:39:55,200 --> 00:39:57,520
Did the gate security say who sent it?

914
00:39:57,840 --> 00:40:00,200
I asked him, and he said
it was an ordinary courier.

915
00:40:02,240 --> 00:40:03,040
I see. Put it here.

916
00:41:01,720 --> 00:41:04,400
[May 7, Drugs]

917
00:41:04,640 --> 00:41:07,040
This was sent to me this morning.

918
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:09,920
I've got this

919
00:41:10,280 --> 00:41:11,040
along with the doll.

920
00:41:12,880 --> 00:41:15,560
[May 7, Drugs]

921
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:20,360
Mr. Zhao,

922
00:41:21,120 --> 00:41:22,720
could it be another prank?

923
00:41:22,760 --> 00:41:23,400
Our customs

924
00:41:23,400 --> 00:41:25,560
receive a lot of this false information
every year.

925
00:41:26,240 --> 00:41:27,360
But early this morning,

926
00:41:27,760 --> 00:41:29,000
Customs did receive

927
00:41:29,040 --> 00:41:30,240
a tip from Interpol

928
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:33,360
that smugglers carrying new drugs

929
00:41:33,400 --> 00:41:36,200
would arrive in Binhai on Flight KM997.

930
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:37,440
Chen,

931
00:41:37,720 --> 00:41:38,920
this flight is on your shift.

932
00:41:38,920 --> 00:41:39,760
Keep an eye on it.

933
00:41:42,200 --> 00:41:43,120
Have the police

934
00:41:43,720 --> 00:41:44,920
checked this doll?

935
00:41:45,120 --> 00:41:45,920
Yes.

936
00:41:46,440 --> 00:41:47,560
This doll is not common.

937
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:49,200
It was imported from Japan.

938
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:50,400
It's not cheap.

939
00:41:50,920 --> 00:41:52,480
Public Security is working
with relevant departments

940
00:41:52,520 --> 00:41:53,760
[May 7, Drugs]
to trace the purchase information.

941
00:41:53,760 --> 00:41:54,360
[May 7, Drugs]

942
00:41:55,080 --> 00:41:55,680
Also,

943
00:41:55,680 --> 00:41:56,360
there wasn't much useful info

944
00:41:56,360 --> 00:41:58,120
from the delivery guy either.

945
00:41:58,880 --> 00:42:00,480
The package was first placed
in the express cabinet.

946
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:02,320
Its surveillance was damaged.

947
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:04,560
Then it was delivered by the courier.

948
00:42:05,960 --> 00:42:08,880
The phone number
and order info are fake.

949
00:42:09,200 --> 00:42:11,800
I guess it was purchased online.

950
00:42:12,960 --> 00:42:14,640
This person went to such lengths

951
00:42:14,640 --> 00:42:15,920
to hide the identity

952
00:42:15,920 --> 00:42:17,200
and mail the doll here.

953
00:42:17,520 --> 00:42:19,760
I don't think this looks like a prank.

954
00:42:20,680 --> 00:42:21,480
Look.

955
00:42:21,520 --> 00:42:22,600
[May 7, Drugs]
The word 'drugs'

956
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:24,200
[May 7, Drugs]
was marked in red.

957
00:42:24,360 --> 00:42:26,400
Could this be some hidden information?

958
00:42:28,280 --> 00:42:29,400
Maybe it's just an emphasis?

959
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:30,800
No way. There are just a few words.

960
00:42:30,800 --> 00:42:32,400
They could have all been written in red.

961
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:34,880
And this guy

962
00:42:35,880 --> 00:42:37,200
acts very meticulously.

963
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:38,600
His actions

964
00:42:39,440 --> 00:42:40,760
should all be planned carefully.

965
00:42:41,800 --> 00:42:43,800
Could it be that it is related to red?

966
00:42:43,920 --> 00:42:45,600
Chief, I think it's possible.

967
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:50,720
You two are on duty
at Inbound Passenger Inspection today.

968
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:53,160
We'd rather believe it's real

969
00:42:53,200 --> 00:42:54,240
than risk ignoring it.

970
00:42:54,440 --> 00:42:55,160
Tell the officers

971
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:57,000
to step up their inspections.

972
00:42:57,800 --> 00:42:58,280
Yes.

973
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:35,800
♪There's a place of simple,
everyday warmth♪

974
00:43:36,720 --> 00:43:43,440
♪A door left open
for the wandering soul♪

975
00:43:44,360 --> 00:43:50,880
♪A humble table still warm with love♪

976
00:43:51,120 --> 00:43:54,760
♪After you've tasted every high and low♪

977
00:43:55,040 --> 00:43:58,680
♪Come home, I'll keep you warm♪

978
00:43:59,440 --> 00:44:06,120
♪Where the days begin and end♪

979
00:44:06,840 --> 00:44:13,760
♪A light still on for the ones
who've lost their way♪

980
00:44:14,560 --> 00:44:21,120
♪An embrace waiting just for you♪

981
00:44:21,400 --> 00:44:25,120
♪Through every passing season♪

982
00:44:25,240 --> 00:44:28,920
♪Even if you return with nothing at all♪

983
00:44:29,560 --> 00:44:33,040
♪Turn around and look♪

984
00:44:33,240 --> 00:44:37,040
♪That door's still open♪

985
00:44:37,240 --> 00:44:40,880
♪A light still burning♪

986
00:44:40,960 --> 00:44:44,680
♪Waiting there for you♪

987
00:44:44,840 --> 00:44:48,360
♪Turn around and look♪

988
00:44:48,600 --> 00:44:52,400
♪Someone's still waiting♪

989
00:44:52,600 --> 00:44:56,200
♪Watching the dusk settle in♪

990
00:44:56,280 --> 00:45:00,000
♪Waiting for the break of dawn♪

991
00:45:01,760 --> 00:45:05,400
♪It's always there♪
